ROMAN ARCH CLEAN ENERGY FINANCE LLC









































Clean Energy Finance

























Clean Energy Finance


















Harris Ingram LLP
Business + Intellectual Property Attorneys




 ROMAN ARCH Clean Energy Finance LLC (Roman Arch CEF) provides advisory, capital raising and investment services to the renewable energy industry, broadly defined.This includes the solar PV, wind power, energy efficiency, primarily municipal LED street lighting projects, biomass, and small hydro sectors, as well as technology-oriented concerns. Within the project development community, the firm targets clients throughout the value chain including: investors, both tax and sponsor equity, construction and permanent debt financing sources, installers/EPCs, in addition to project developers at various stages along the development continuum, including post-commissioning. In the United States we have the capability to address all sectors including utility scale solar PV and wind power projects. We also provide services to developers and asset owners in the commercial, industrial, municipal, small-scale utility and distributed generation communities. In all cases Roman Arch CEF looks to develop long-term collaborative partnerships with its clients.At this time we are primarily focused on solar PV, municipal LED street lighting, small hydro and wind power projects and assets. However, we are also interested in being of assistance to parties focused on other existing or emerging renewable energy assets and technologies. We are primarily focused on markets within the Western Hemisphere including the United States, Canada, Mexico, Latin America and the Caribbean (LAC). We are very active internationally across all sectors. We have in the past been active in Europe, most notably Italy and Germany. Our efforts in Europe have been predominately associated with the secondary market; providing M&A services and advice to owners of grid-connected operating assets. We have an active and extensive network of private equity and infrastructure funds, utilities, independent power producers (IPPs) and corporates. With respect to other international locales, in particular LAC, the Middle East and North African region (MENA), as well as South Africa, we have extensive relationships in the international development community that can be instrumental in supporting projects in developing markets around the world. We are also well-positioned to provide advice and education regarding, and access to, the various U.S government agencies such as the EX-IM Bank, OPIC, USAID, and the Department of Commerce, among others, that are designed to facilitate the export of U.S. green energy technologies. Furthermore, we have well-developed relationships with various advisory firms and multilateral development banks, including the IDB (IIC and MIF), CAF, CDC, ADB, the World Bank Group and the IFC, that leverage renewable energy investments as an international development vehicle. In ancient Rome, as legend has it, Roman engineers stood behind their work by standing beneath the archway they designed, just as the keystone was being dropped into place. If the arch collapsed, so did their business, so to speak. I've always liked and appreciated this story. The words ROMAN ARCH were chosen to be prominent in the name of our firm to exemplify this same commitment to excellence we strive for on behalf of our clients. We stand firmly behind the advice we impart to our clients with our success being inextricably tied to their success as well.









